<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 11:43AM CST  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL ESCAMBIA...SOUTHWESTERN
CONECUH AND NORTH CENTRAL ESCAMBIA COUNTIES THROUGH 1230 PM CST...
At 1142 AM CST, broadcast media reported a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of I65 And AL 21, or 7 miles northwest of Flomaton, moving
northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Pea to half inch size hail.
SOURCE...Broadcast media.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Atmore, Brewton, Century, Flomaton, East Brewton, Castleberry,
Pollard, I65 And US 84, I65 And CR 1, I65 And AL 113, I65 And AL 21,
and Poarch Creek Reservation.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
